title: Women's TT Clinic Presented by Boise VeloWomen
18th Annual Barking Spider Bash
description: 18th Barking Spider XC--desert classic race course! choose from 9-27miles of off road fun.
course: The 2014 Spider race features a fun, easy, 9 mile lap course with rolling terrain and terrific spectator viewing. The course includes the imfamous "Skateboard Park" descent, a twisting, turning tunnel of thrills. There is a new climbing section near the end of the course, so you might want to inspect?
notes:
START TIMES:
CAT 3 Beginners (1 lap) and Trailblazers (1/4 lap) - 11:40 pm 
CAT 2 Sports (2 laps) - 11:35pm 
CAT 1 Experts (3 laps) - 11:30pm 
Pros (3 laps) - 11:29pm 
Kids under 10 race (free) - 2:15pm.
directions:
Here are detailed directions to the Spider:
Take 2nd Nampa exit (whether coming from east or west) Go south over freeway to Garriety, turn right go under railroad tracks, then turn left, and then right on 12th Avenue South. Follow SIGNS toward Murphy & Melba out past hospital, 15 miles after leaving Nampa the road will drop down to the Snake River, where you will cross over the bridge BEARING to the left at the "Y" towards Murphy 3/4 of a mile after crossing river, turn right on Reynolds Creek Road - go 1.5 miles (keep driving thru stinky Dairy Farm) and event is on the right-hand-side at the Hemingway ORV area.

title: 2014 Ronde Van Ketchum
description: A fun ride / tour around almost every hill within Ketchum, North of Ketchum, Sun Valley, and Elkhorn.
course: The full course is just under 122km and includes 1433m of climbing.
registration:
$20 CASH only entry fee.

You must fill out and sign a USA Cycling Non Competitive Release.  

Sign up is available at the Perch or durance up until Friday, June 20, 2014 18:00.

No event day sign up.

Souvenir wattle bottle to the first 100 to sign up.
notes:
The event starts promptly at 0900 in front of durance.
durance is located at 131 Second St / Ketchum / ID
N43.679254 W114.36464

After the event, at 1500, you are invited to a post event pizza and drinks at the Elephant's Perch.
The Perch is located at  280 East Ave / Ketchum / ID
N43.68174 W114.362417
directions:
Start is at durance.
Finish is at the Perch.

title: Tamarack Resort Bike Fest
description: 3 stage enduro ride. Using lift access at Tamarack Resort. Bike specific trails with awesome flow. Runs are 5-15min long.
course: No extreme riding. Everything can be ridden on a trail or XC bike. 6in bikes usually win all!
registration:
http://www.webscorer.com/register?raceid=10614
Early Registration thru AUGUST 1
Pro/Cat 1 = $45
Cat 2-3 = $40
Junior = $25
Onsite Registration Aug. 2-3
Pro/Ex = $50
Sport, Beginner = $45
Junior = $25
Lift tickets are seperate $20.00 cash or check please.
notes: This may be the only chance to ride Tamarack lifts this summer. Dont miss out on a unique opportunity utilizing quality trails.
directions: To get to Tamarack from Boise, Id. Head North on HWY55 to Donnelly, take a left on Roseberry rd. Follow the signs South til you find the resort on your right hand side of the road.

title: OctoberFest 3
description: CrosstoberFest 3, A two day cyclocross event in beautiful Sandpoint Idaho. CrosstoberFest is part of the Wildwest Cx Series.
course: Two courses same location. We have a dedicated Cx course that keeps getting better. Come experience Shelob's Liar. You will enter but you might not come out.
registration: You can register day or race or pre-register here. Registration order determines start order for the first race. After that series position determines call ups.
notes: This is a two day event. There is camping at the race site.
directions: Sadnpoint Idaho is located 50 minutes north of Coeur d'Alene Idaho. The address of the course is 2105 N Boyer Ave, Sandpoint, ID 83864
